# Rust build output
/target

# The schema crate (crates/entl-schema) is its own single-crate workspace and a
# codegen-time TOOL, not part of entl's runtime. It reaches the fluessig derive
# crates through a `fluessig/` symlink → $FLUESSIG_DIR that scripts/gen.sh creates
# at codegen time (mirroring how the downstream fluessig-gen stage is located).
# The symlink, its build dir, and its lockfile are all machine-local, never
# committed — so the root `cargo build` / `rust` CI job never tries to resolve a
# fluessig path dep with no checkout, and the codegen-freshness gate stays clean.
/crates/entl-schema/fluessig
/crates/entl-schema/target
/crates/entl-schema/Cargo.lock

# DuckDB databases
*.duckdb
*.duckdb.wal

# OS / editor
.DS_Store

# vale-synced style packages (keep vocab config)
styles/*
!styles/config
